    "title": "Applying the Data Ethics Canvas",
    "displayTitle": "Applying the Data Ethics Canvas",
    "body": "<p dir=\"ltr\">The Data Ethics Canvas is a tool for anyone who collects, shares or uses data. It helps identify and manage ethical issues – at the start of a project that uses data, and throughout.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">It encourages you to ask important questions about projects that use data, and reflect on the responses. These might be:</p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\">What is your primary purpose for using data in this project?</p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\">Who could be negatively affected by this project?</p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\">The Data Ethics Canvas provides a framework to develop ethical guidance that suits any context, whatever the project’s size or scope. There is guidance and support for using the <a href=\"https://www.theodi.org/article/the-data-ethics-canvas-2021/\" target=\"_blank\">Data Ethics Canvas on the ODI website</a>, shared under an open licence.</p>",
