    "title": "Building trust through data ethics",
    "displayTitle": "Building trust through data ethics",
    "body": "<div class=\"barclays-container\"><p>Let’s take a look at an example of the Data Ethics Canvas being used in practice.</p><p>Barclays UK wants to work with data in a way that <span class=\"highlight\">builds trust</span> with customers and society. They also want to document their decisions around data and data ethics in a standardised, consistent way.</p><blockquote>It’s important for customers to trust us with their data at the same level as they do with their money.</blockquote><p>To achieve this goal, Barclays decided to use the <span class=\"highlight\">Data Ethics Canvas</span>...</p><p>The Data Ethics Canvas has been fully embraced, enabling Barclays to build up a substantial library of use cases...</p><p>Barclays UK received external recognition of its work in this field, having won the ‘Best Data and AI Ethics Initiative’ category in the 2021 DataIQ Awards.</p></div>",
    "_id": "650da0f294389ef9d9f97556",
