    "title": "Summary",
    "displayTitle": "Summary",
    "body": "<p>The Data Ethics Canvas is a practical tool for guiding discussions within data project teams, assisting them in assessing the ethical implications of their work on individuals and society. It comprises four key sections that support ethical considerations from project inception through its lifecycle, prompting essential questions about data usage goals and potential harm to stakeholders.<br /><br />The canvas allows the documentation of decisions, helps guide data projects, and enhances confidence and trust in ethical decision-making.</p>",
